cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.DC

This paper deals with networked control systems and their vulnerabilities to attacks, making it likely to fall under the categories of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper introduces a control-theoretic framework for modeling the wormhole attack, which suggests a possible fit under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the impact of the wormhole attack on network flows and delays, which could place it under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
